# Documentation

Update `README.md` when you add features, API routes, env vars, dependencies, deployment changes, or modify project structure.

## README sections to touch

- Features, Tech Stack, Site Structure, Project Structure
- Setup instructions (local + production) with troubleshooting
- Environment variables (secret vs public)
- Available scripts

## Cursor plans

Plans that implement features must include a todo to update README with specific sections and any new setup steps.

## Changelog

**Never manually edit `docs/CHANGELOG.md`** — semantic-release generates it on merge to `main`.
